 - id: rrp-004
   text: 'The path reveals itself to those who follow the YAML.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: automation
   level: beginner
   tags: [yaml, configuration, infrastructure-as-code]
   teaches: 'Trust configuration as the source of truth.'
   source: 'Koan of Configuration'
   related: [ops-001]

 - id: rrp-005
   text: 'The wise instructor grades with tools, not toil. The foolish instructor toils without tools.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: philosophy
   level: beginner
   tags: [automation, tools, efficiency]
   teaches: 'Leverage automation to reduce manual labor.'
   source: 'The Tao of the Grader'
   related: [qa-001]

 - id: rrp-006
   text: 'The tool that finishes is superior to the tool that is perfect.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: philosophy
   level: advanced
   tags: [pragmatism, shipping, perfectionism]
   teaches: 'Completion beats perfection in operational contexts.'
   source: 'The Three Truths'
   related: [rrp-003]

 - id: rrp-007
   text: 'Clone shallow, grade deep. The wise instructor needs not the full history to see the present.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: cloning
   level: intermediate
   tags: [git, efficiency, shallow-clone]
   teaches: 'Use shallow clones to save bandwidth and time when history is irrelevant.'
   source: 'The Tao of the Developer'
   related: [git-001]

 - id: rrp-008
   text: 'The temporary is eternal in its purposeâ€”it serves and vanishes, leaving only results.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: cleanup
   level: advanced
   tags: [ephemeral, cleanup, purpose]
   teaches: 'Respect ephemeral resources by cleaning them up.'
   source: 'The Tao of the Developer'
   related: [rrp-001]

 - id: rrp-009
   text: "Process many, keep none. The master's disk remains empty, yet knowledge flows to reports."
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: batch
   level: master
   tags: [batch, storage, data-flow]
   teaches: 'Data should flow through the system, not stagnate on disk.'
   source: 'The Tao of the Developer'
   related: [rrp-002]

 - id: rrp-010
   text: 'The YAML already contains the path. The instructor need only read it.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: automation
   level: intermediate
   tags: [yaml, discovery, data-driven]
   teaches: 'Data-driven discovery prevents manual entry errors.'
   source: 'Koans for the Rushed Instructor'
   related: [rrp-004]

 - id: rrp-011
   text: 'Documentation unread is documentation unwritten. But documentation unwritten is failure guaranteed.'
   section: qa-tooling
   subsection: documentation
   level: intermediate
   tags: [documentation, communication, failure]
   teaches: 'Documentation is a prerequisite for success, even if reading it is optional.'
   source: 'The Tao of the Developer'
   related: [qa-002]

 - id: rrp-012
   text: 'The README that saves one question saves a thousand emails.'
   section: qa-tooling
   subsection: documentation
   level: beginner
   tags: [documentation, efficiency, scaling]
   teaches: 'Good documentation scales your time.'
   source: 'The Tao of the Developer'
   related: [qa-002]

 - id: rrp-013
   text: 'Tests guard the code. Mocks stand in for the cloud. Confidence grows strong.'
   section: qa-tooling
   subsection: quality
   level: intermediate
   tags: [testing, mocks, haiku]
   teaches: 'Testing strategies for cloud dependencies.'
   source: 'Koan of Confidence'
   related: [qa-003]

 - id: rrp-014
   text: 'One report to rule them all, one chart to find them. In darkness bind them, in HTML light.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: batch
   level: intermediate
   tags: [reporting, visualization, humor]
   teaches: 'Consolidated reporting brings clarity to batch processes.'
   source: 'Koan of Clarity'
   related: [rrp-002]

 - id: rrp-015
   text: 'The repo is temporary; the grade is permanent.'
   section: remote-repo
   subsection: philosophy
   level: beginner
   tags: [persistence, ephemeral, priorities]
   teaches: 'Distinguish between the artifact and the value derived from it.'
   source: 'The Three Truths'
   related: [rrp-008]

